The latest statistics from MTN and Vodacom reveal that the Hisense U961 is the most used smartphone on South African networks. While high-end smartphones like the Samsung Galaxy S10 and Apple iPhone dominate the news, more affordable smartphones dominate sales in South Africa. The Hisense U961, Samsung Galaxy J5 Prime, and Vodacom Smart Kicka 4 – all affordable devices – are the most used on local networks. Considering the high demand for cheap smartphones in South Africa, it is no surprise that MTN recently launched its Smart S 3G phone, priced at around R300. The list below provides an overview of the most popular smartphones for prepaid users on MTN’s network. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-298724 lazyload" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Hisense-U962.jpg" alt="" data-aspectratio="640/427" width="640" height="427" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Hisense-U962.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Hisense-U962-600x400.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /><noscript><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-298724" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Hisense-U962.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="427" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Hisense-U962.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Hisense-U962-600x400.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-298732" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Mobicell-Rebel.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="427" srcset="https://m